CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 22, 1967, pg. 19, reads: "Men's Program Specialists - During the recent Men's Day observance at Homewood AME Zion Church the program featured a panel of church and community leaders. Pictured left to right they are, Charles Bailey, local radio newscaster, moderator; and Adolphus Patterson, Bernard H. Jones, URA director; William R. Montgomery, health consultant, Duquesne University; John H. Adams, officer; Business and Job Development; Robert L. Bolden, URA project coordinator, Homewood.  The Rev. George A. Fitch, pastor of the church, stands at the right.  'The Negro Man in His Community' was the topic for discussion. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Panel at Men's Day service, from left: Charles Bailey, Adolphus Patterson, Bernard H. Jones, William R. Montgomery, John H. Adams, Robert L. Bolden, and Rev. George Fitch standing on right, in Homewood AME Zion Church
